{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781952810,"nonce":"BQOLudaeIiY4MtMYDCuMSVJlom8=","title":"Allow more than one use of the same input","message":"Consider the command below. The `messages` input is used more than once. This is a valid use case. But, ccwl only picks the first use of `messages` and ignores the rest.\n```scheme\n(command #:inputs (messages #:type (array string))\n         #:run \"echo\" messages (array messages #:separator \",\"))\n```\nConsequently, any errors in later uses of `messages` should be reported too. For example below, the separator is not a string and should be reported.\n```scheme\n(command #:inputs (messages #:type (array string))\n         #:run \"echo\" messages (array messages #:separator foo))\n```","files":null}]}